text: Arthur John Gray was a athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== He competed for England in the high jump and triple jump at the 1934 British Empire Games in London. He was the 1931 high jump AAA champion and 1932 triple jump AAA champion. ==References== Category:English male high jumpers Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1934 British Empire Games Category:English male triple jumpers
title: Arthur Gray (athlete)
